OPT-Neuro Motion Report

This summarizes the MRIQC metrics for framewise displacement, a measure of motion, in OPT-Neuro. It is only examining resting state fMRI scans. This document does not report the quality of structural scans.

The chart below shows how the percentage of scan timepoints above the 0.5mm threshold has changed over time. Each dot represents one run in the scanner - a participant usually has two runs per timepoint. The vertical line represents the date of the RA call to discuss strategies to mitigate in-scanner motion.

The horizontal green line at 35% represents a typical threshold for data quality: points that lie below the green line are the most likely to be suitable for analysis. Sites should aim to shift their above-threshold motion %-ages below the green line.
